                <h1>Effortlessly Send Processes to Background in Linux</h1>
                <p>To send a process to the background in Linux, you can use the keyboard shortcut Ctrl + Z while the process is running in the foreground. This suspends the process. Then, type `bg` to continue its execution in the background. To see all background processes, use the `jobs` command, and to bring one back to the foreground, use `fg %job_number`.</p>
